cq_recognize_Frieze_group


  1. Question

    There are 7 different Frieze groups. I depicted them below with their IUC names and Conway nicknames.


    For each of the patterns below, determine the Frieze group.

    Pattern 1


    Match the IUC name:

    Pattern 2


    Match the Conway nickname:



    Solution

    • The first pattern is a p11m (which is also called jump).
    • The second pattern is a spinning sidle (which is also called p2mg).
